This solution works by iterating over each tile in the circle and checking if it forms an alternating group with its neighbors. The `%n` operation is used to wrap around to the start of the circle when we reach the end. We count the number of tiles that form an alternating group and then divide by 2 at the end because each group is counted twice (once for each tile in the group).

